The Vice President, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the White House to commemorate the first anniversary of the United States Space Force. He thanked the President for his enthusiasm and dedication to establishing the Space Force and recognized the contributions of various military leaders and members of Congress who supported its creation. Pence highlighted the growth and accomplishments of the Space Force over the past year, including the recruitment of over 2,000 military members and the establishment of two Space Force installations. He emphasized the importance of space as a warfighting domain and the need to defend American interests and freedom in space. Pence announced that the members of the Space Force will now be known as "Guardians" and concluded his remarks by expressing gratitude and confidence in the Guardians' mission to ensure American dominance in space.